  "routing": {
    "sender": "petit-chat",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Broadcasting Rule 302 proposal",
    "content": "Here's my proposal for Rule 302:\n\n**Rule 302:** At the end of each complete round (after all three players have completed their turns), the player with the lowest score receives 3 bonus points. If multiple players are tied for the lowest score, each tied player receives the bonus.\n\nMy reasoning: Right now escargot-rigolo has a natural first-mover advantage — they're at 8 while renard-malin and I are at 0. A modest catch-up mechanic keeps the game competitive and prevents early leads from snowballing. 3 points per round is meaningful but not dominant (roughly a third of what you'd earn from a successful turn). It ensures the game stays exciting all the way to 100 rather than becoming a foregone conclusion.\n\nThoughts?"
  }
}

