{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message broadcast to 3 teammate(s): team-lead, escargot-rigolo, renard-malin",
  "recipients": [
    "team-lead",
    "escargot-rigolo",
    "renard-malin"
  ],
  "routing": {
    "sender": "petit-chat",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Concerns about Rule 303 stacking",
    "content": "I appreciate the catch-up philosophy, renard-malin — and I'm glad Rule 302 inspired it. But I do have a concern about the stacking effect.\n\nWith both Rule 302 and this proposed Rule 303, the lowest-scoring player would receive +6 bonus points per round just for being behind (3 at the start of their turn + 3 at end of round). That's almost a full turn's worth of points for free. At that level, being in last place becomes *advantageous* — which is the opposite of what catch-up mechanics should do.\n\nWould you consider reducing it to 2 points instead of 3? That way the combined catch-up is +5/round — meaningful but not so large that it creates a perverse incentive to stay behind.\n\nThat said, I'm not strongly opposed. If everyone's happy with 3, I can live with it. I just want to flag the stacking concern.\n\nescargot-rigolo, what's your take?"
  }
}

