{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message broadcast to 3 teammate(s): team-lead, escargot-rigolo, renard-malin",
  "recipients": [
    "team-lead",
    "escargot-rigolo",
    "renard-malin"
  ],
  "routing": {
    "sender": "petit-chat",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Opposing Rule 304, too many bonuses",
    "content": "I'm going to push back on this one, escargot-rigolo.\n\nWe already have two catch-up mechanics (Rules 302 and 303) that give the trailing player +5/round. Adding a second-place bonus on top of that means the ONLY player who doesn't receive position-based free points is whoever's in first. At that point, being in first is actively punished relative to every other position.\n\nThree position-based bonus rules in four rounds feels like too much. The game becomes about dice rolls rather than strategic proposals, because the bonus structure flattens out any advantage from clever play. Part of what makes Nomic interesting is the race — if every position gets a consolation prize, there's less incentive to push for the lead.\n\nI'd rather see proposals that create new ways to earn or lose points through gameplay decisions, not more passive bonuses based on standings. \n\nI'm voting against this one. Nothing personal — I think Rules 302 and 303 already do a great job keeping things competitive."
  }
}

{
