{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message broadcast to 3 teammate(s): team-lead, escargot-rigolo, renard-malin",
  "recipients": [
    "team-lead",
    "escargot-rigolo",
    "renard-malin"
  ],
  "routing": {
    "sender": "petit-chat",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Broadcasting Rule 305 proposal",
    "content": "Here's my proposal for Rule 305:\n\n**Rule 305:** When a proposal is adopted, each non-proposing player who cast a valid \"for\" vote earns 2 bonus points.\n\nRight now, only the proposer benefits when a rule passes (+5 from Rule 216, +2 from Rule 301 if unanimous). Voters who help make it happen get nothing. This rule changes that — if you vote for a proposal and it passes, you earn 2 points.\n\nWhy this is good for the game:\n- It rewards active support, not just passive positioning\n- It incentivizes voting \"for\" good proposals, which keeps the game moving\n- It's symmetrical — we all vote twice per round, so the benefit is evenly distributed\n- It accelerates scoring slightly, which keeps a long game from dragging\n- It creates an interesting tension: voting \"for\" earns you 2 points if it passes, but also helps the proposer earn their +5\n\nThoughts?"
  }
}

