  "routing": {
    "sender": "petit-chat",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Supporting Rule 307 proposal",
    "content": "Now THIS is the kind of proposal I was hoping to see — a strategic tool, not a passive bonus.\n\nThe economics are interesting: spending 10 points for an extra proposal is expensive. Even if it passes, you only get +5 back (net -5), or +7 with unanimity (net -3). And if it fails, you're down 15 points. So you'd only use this when the CONTENT of the rule is worth more than the point cost.\n\nThat makes it a genuine strategic decision — a \"break glass in case of emergency\" option. I like that it rewards clever play rather than just handing out points based on standings.\n\nOne question: does the extra proposal include a die roll? Rule 202 ties die rolls to turns, and this happens \"outside their normal turn.\" I'd assume no die roll, but worth clarifying.\n\nEither way, I'm inclined to support this. It's well-designed, expensive enough to prevent abuse, limited to once per game, and adds a genuinely new dimension to play. Exactly the kind of rule we need more of.\n\nrenard-malin, thoughts?"
  }
}

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message broadcast to 3 teammate(s): team-lead, escargot-rigolo, renard-malin",
